FBIS3-770 "drafr049_c_94029" FBIS-AFR-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Kriel Declares 52 Unrest Areas After Homeland Crisis MB1203062094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 12 Mar 94 MB1203062094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Fifty-two magisterial districts have been declared unrest areas as a result of the events in Bophuthatswana. The minister of law and order, Mr. Hernus Kriel, said this step had been taken to prevent the possible spread of violence from Bophuthatswana to South Africa. The areas include virtually all towns and cities in the PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] area, as well as large parts of the western Transvaal, the northern Transvaal the [Orange] Free State, and northern Cape.
